comment: Gibson (CHI) wraps up Mahinmi (IND) underneath the basket during the rebound attempt.
George (IND) obtains a legal guarding position and beats Snell (CHI) to the spot before he begins his upward shooting motion.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Butler (CHI) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Moore (CHI) makes incidental contact that does not affect Ellis' (IND) RSBQ on the drive.
Gibson (CHI) jumps vertically and legally contests Ellis' (IND) shot attempt.
RHH shows that Mahinmi (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Butler's (CHI) driving layup attempt.
Gibson (CHI) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Moore (CHI) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Butler (CHI) makes "high five" contact with the George's (IND) hand during his follow-through, which is legal since the contact is incidental to the block.
